Amurka ta kara yawan kudaden da take bayarwa don bunkasa ilimin kere kere
Idan aka yi la'akari da karuwar ayyukan kasar Sin a fannin ilimin kere kere, to ya kamata Amurka ta ninka kudaden da take kashewa wajen bincike a fannin, in ji mai zuba jari kuma mai aikin kere kere Kai-Fu Lee, wanda ya yi aiki a Google, Microsoft da Apple.
Wannan jawabin ya biyo bayan sanarwar AI daga bangarori daban-daban na gwamnatin Amurka, duk da cewa Amurka gaba daya ba ta da tsarin dabarun AI.
A halin yanzu, kasar Sin ta gabatar da shirinta na shekara ta bara, inda ta yi niyyar zama kasa ta farko a fannin kirkirar kere kere ta hanyar fasaha nan da shekarar 2030.
"Abin farin ciki ne cewa, a yanzu, akwai wasu ƙasashe da suke da ƙarancin ci gaba a harkokin fasaha, amma ba a san ko su nawa ne ba.
Haɗa kuɗin zai iya ninka damar samun babbar nasarar AI a Amurka, Lee ya ce a cikin wata hira da CNBC a wannan makon.
Lee, wanda littafinsa mai suna AI Superpowers: China, Silicon Valley and the New World Order ya fito ne a wannan watan daga Houghton Mifflin Harcourt, shi ne Shugaba na kamfanin Sinovation Ventures, wanda ya zuba jari a daya daga cikin manyan kamfanonin fasaha na AI a China, Face++.
A shekarun 1980s, ya yi aiki a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon a kan tsarin AI wanda ya doke dan wasan Othello na Amurka mafi girma, daga baya ya zama babban jami'in gudanarwa a Microsoft Research da kuma shugaban kamfanin Google a China.
Lee ya yaba wa gasar fasahar gwamnatin Amurka da ta gabata kamar Gasar Robotics Challenge na Hukumar Ci Gaban Bincike ta Tsaro (DARPA) kuma ya tambaya game da lokacin gasar ta gaba, saboda yana son taimakawa wajen gano masu hangen nesa na gaba.
Lee ya ce masu bincike a Amirka sukan yi aiki tuƙuru don su samu tallafin gwamnati.
"Ba kasar Sin ce ke cire manyan jami'ai ba, kamfanoni ne", in ji Lee.
Facebook, Google da sauran kamfanonin fasaha sun yi amfani da 'yan kwararru daga jami'o'i a cikin 'yan shekarun nan don yin aiki a kan AI.
Lee ya ce, sauya manufofin shige da fice na Amurka na iya taimakawa wajen inganta kokarin da Amurka ke yi na fasaha.
"Ina ganin cewa ya kamata a ba da katin kore ga waɗanda suka sami digiri a fannin AI", in ji shi.
A watan Yulin shekarar 2017, majalisar kasar Sin ta gabatar da shirin bunkasa fasahar kere kere ta gaba (Next Generation Artificial Intelligence Development Plan).
Lee ya ce, National Natural Science Foundation of China tana ba da tallafi ga masu ilimi kamar yadda National Science Foundation da sauran hukumomin gwamnati ke ba da tallafi ga masu binciken Amurka, amma ingancin aikin kimiyya a China ya fi ƙasa.
A farkon wannan shekarar, Ma'aikatar Tsaro ta Amurka ta kafa Cibiyar Haɗin Kai na Artificial Intelligence, wanda abokan hulɗa daga masana'antu da kimiyya za su shiga, kuma fadar White House ta sanar da kafa kwamitin musamman kan ilimin kere kere.
Har ila yau, DARPA ta sanar a wannan watan cewa za ta zuba dala biliyan biyu a shirin AI Next.
Gidauniyar Kimiyya ta Ƙasa (NSF) a yanzu tana zuba fiye da dala miliyan 100 a shekara a bincike kan fasaha ta wucin gadi.
A halin yanzu, babu wani mataki da aka dauka a kan dokokin Amurka game da kafa hukumar tsaro ta kasa kan ilimin kere kere na tsawon watanni.
