HIV/AIDS: China ta ba da rahoton ƙaruwar sabbin cututtuka da kashi 14 cikin ɗari
China ta sanar da karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan mutanen da ke da cutar HIV ko AIDS.
Ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya sun ce fiye da mutane 820,000 ne ke fama da cutar a ƙasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane kusan 40,000.
A wani bangare kuma, yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun faru ne ta hanyar jima'i.
A dā, cutar HIV tana yaɗuwa da sauri a wasu ɓangarorin ƙasar Sin ta wurin ƙarin jini da ke ɗauke da cutar.
Amma, adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na ƙasar Sin a wani taro da aka yi a lardin Yunnan.
Amma a shekara guda, adadin mutanen da suke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya ƙaru da 100,000 a ƙasar Sin.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i na da matukar damuwa a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An cire laifukan luwadi a kasar Sin a 1997, amma ana zargin cewa nuna bambanci ga 'yan LGBT ya zama ruwan dare.
Saboda ra'ayoyin da suka dace da al'adun ƙasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70-90 na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza suna yin aure da mata.
Yawancin kamuwa da cuta suna zuwa ne daga rashin kāriya a lokacin jima'i a cikin waɗannan alaƙa.
Tun 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da magungunan cutar HIV ga kowa domin magance matsalar.
